{
  "text": "Another possible approach to the relative case of GKD theorem goes as follows. This time the arcs considered are not points in the space of arcs X \u221e , but in the relative space of arcs J \u221e (X/Y ) ( [CITATION_1] ). First we remind some basic definitions and properties.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "35183336",
    "15782559"
  ],
  "bib_entries": {
    "15782559": {
      "title": "Versal deformations of formal arcs",
      "abstract": "Let X be a complex algebraic variety, and L(X) be the scheme of formal arcs in X. Let f be an arc whose image is not contained in the singularities of X. We show that the formal neighborhood of f in L(X) admits a decomposition into a product of an infinite-dimensional smooth piece, and a piece isomorphic to the formal neighborhood of a closed point of a scheme of finite type."
    },
    "35183336": {
      "title": "Jets via Hasse-Schmidt derivations",
      "abstract": "This note is intended to provide a general reference for jet spaces and jet differentials, valid in maximal generality (at the level of EGA). The approach is rather concrete, using Hasse-Schmidt (divided) higher differentials. Discussion of projectivized jet spaces (as in Green and Griffiths (1980)) is included."
    }
  }
}